&lt;p&gt;BeyondTrust is a place where you can bring your purpose to life through the work that you do, creating a safer world through our cybersecurity SaaS portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our culture of flexibility, trust, and continual learning means you will be recognized for your growth, and for the impact you make on our success. You will be surrounded by people who challenge, support, and inspire you to be the best version of yourself.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;This is a hybrid position (3 days in the Tel Aviv office, 2 days work from home - negotiable)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;The Role&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior UX designer will have an integral role within BeyondTrust, responsible for supporting the UX team to ensure consistent, effective, and competitive user experiences, whilst being a role model for other UX team members. &amp;nbsp;The Senior UX designer will also be expected to collaborate with cross-functional departments (i.e. Product Management, Marketing, Engineering) to help identify specific user needs and work with developers, domain specialists, and a content writer to deliver technically feasible, user-focused solutions that align with business goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with clients directly to understand their business environment, processes and ‘jobs to be done’ and obtain their feedback and direction on&amp;nbsp;product&amp;nbsp;interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Director of Product Design in roadmap creation and project planning&amp;nbsp;and prioritizing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the&amp;nbsp;UX&amp;nbsp;design practice by actively seeking process improvements, driving productive change and running exercises to encourage widespread UX adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the UX team by sharing experiences and skills, running team workshops and identifying exercises, events and courses to support team progression.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate product interfaces with competitive and best-in-class interfaces to drive continuous improvement in the&amp;nbsp;portfolio product’s&amp;nbsp;UI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the&amp;nbsp;UX design&amp;nbsp;team in creating user flows, wireframes, high-fidelity mockups, and clickable prototypes to iterate on design direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide the&amp;nbsp;UX&amp;nbsp;team in refining the visual language of our&amp;nbsp;products and&amp;nbsp;expanding our design&amp;nbsp;system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with cross-functional business and technical teams and key stakeholders to define&amp;nbsp;highly effective, usable, and consistent user interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design elegant solutions&amp;nbsp;and simple&amp;nbsp;to complex workflows&amp;nbsp;leveraging client iterative validation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the user advocate during the&amp;nbsp;development process and offer&amp;nbsp;suggestions from a&amp;nbsp;user-centered&amp;nbsp;perspective.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product Managers,&amp;nbsp;Development,&amp;nbsp;QA,&amp;nbsp;SEs,&amp;nbsp;and customers to ensure UI meets product requirements and experience expectations. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a key player during the QA testing process to ensure the user experience requirements are fulfilled.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the&amp;nbsp;UX&amp;nbsp;“go to”&amp;nbsp;in the local development office&amp;nbsp;with in-depth knowledge of user interface best practices, company&amp;nbsp;design system&amp;nbsp;standards, and supportive research to direct recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;What You’ll Bring&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6&amp;nbsp;or more years of user experience&amp;nbsp;design experience&amp;nbsp;for desktop&amp;nbsp;software,&amp;nbsp;web applications,&amp;nbsp;mobile platforms and other standard technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in mentoring and/or leading teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to mentor UX Designers, and to provide guidance to bring out their best work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort in working with remote distributed teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong written and verbal communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong conceptualization ability, strong visual communication ability and attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capacity to act on immediate needs while building for the&amp;nbsp;long-term&amp;nbsp;vision and strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of common software development practices and proficiency working within a software development lifecycle (SDLC).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced experience in using Figma design tool, including auto-layout and interactive prototyping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to&amp;nbsp;balance&amp;nbsp;UX design&amp;nbsp;team mentoring, hands-on UX work, and&amp;nbsp;provide&amp;nbsp;input for product decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter; eager and able to quickly learn new technologies&amp;nbsp;and approaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can&amp;nbsp;successfully&amp;nbsp;build&amp;nbsp;and maintain relationships with developers and&amp;nbsp;managers, as well as&amp;nbsp;champion the&amp;nbsp;UX&amp;nbsp;team’s ideas within the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be&amp;nbsp;self-reliant but&amp;nbsp;be able to communicate and contribute in a&amp;nbsp;remote&amp;nbsp;team setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Nice To Have&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;UNIX, Linux,&amp;nbsp;Windows, and Mac OS experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Android, iOS, Windows Mobile,&amp;nbsp;other&amp;nbsp;mobile platform experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;User experience&amp;nbsp;design experience&amp;nbsp;for enterprise cyber security software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Jira, Claude Design, Adobe Creative Suite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to organize, multitask and prioritize.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Better Together&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Diversity. Inclusion. They’re more than just words for us. They are the guiding values of how we build our teams, cultivate leaders, and create a culture where people feel connected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We take care of our employees so they can take care of our customers. Customers who&amp;nbsp;come from all walks of life just like us. We hire incredible people from diverse backgrounds because when we are different together, we are stronger together.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;About Us&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BeyondTrust is the global identity security leader protecting Paths to Privilege™. Our identity-centric approach goes beyond securing privileges and access, empowering organizations with the most effective solution to manage the entire identity attack surface and neutralize threats, whether from external attacks or insiders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BeyondTrust is leading the charge in transforming identity security to prevent breaches and limit the blast radius of attacks, while creating a superior customer experience and operational efficiencies. We are trusted by 20,000 customers, including 75 of the Fortune 100, and our global ecosystem of partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Learn more at &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.beyondtrust.com/&quot;&gt;www.beyondtrust.com&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
